==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grum
<hw>Grum</hw> <pr>(gr⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Dan.
<ets>grum</ets> furious, Sw. <ets>grym</ets>, AS. <ets>gram</ets>, and
E. <ets>grim</ets>, and <ets>grumble</ets>. ⟦root⟧35.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Morose; severe of countenance; sour; surly; glum; grim.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Nick looked sour and <xex>grum</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Arbuthnof.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Low; deep in the throat; guttural; rumbling; <as>as,
a <ex>grum</ex> voice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grumble</ent>⟦br⟧
